		<title>06LIFE FOR PARENTS - CONTINUED</title>
		<content> Most farmers have sons who have an    
 interest in the land. Mixed farming,  
 making of hay and silage wre their    
 main pursuits; about 1 in 4 employed  
 help at some time in the week. Nearly 
 all the men visited a market each week
 if only to compare prices and to talk 
 over current events. Few men go       
 shopping with their wives; more than  
 formerly go on holiday with the       
 family.(Surveyed at a NFU meeting).   
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
